animal.name: Ruby
animal.description:
Say hello to Ruby! Miss Ruby is a one and a half year old Staffordshire terrier. This precious girl was found by her foster mom sadly abandoned in a crate on the side of the road. She

is a sweet and

loving dog despite her ruff past. Her favorite activities include cuddling on the couch

, eating, and going for walks. Ruby is housetrained and working on basic commands

like sit and down. She is crate-trained and doesn't mind lounging there in her comfy bed while you're away.

Although she's over a year old, Ruby

still has plenty of p

uppy energy and typically g

reets people with the same, enthusiastic, puppy joy

and may try to wiggle into laps and lick faces. She is eager to please, quick to respond to corrections, and will be easy to train.

Ruby is adjusting well to home life after being abandoned and spending some time at the shelter. She loves all people and meeting new people is fun and exciting. She's a curious dog and loves to explore, but at the same time can be timid in new situations and easily startled. With training and socialization in her new home, Ruby's confidence and spirit will continue to blossom.

1 1/2 years old

house trained

crate trained

good with big and small humans (babies unknown)

good with dogs of all sizes

heartworm negative

the BEST ears and tiny jowlies

loves belly rubs and ear rubs

NO cats or small animals

Please contact us at PacoCorpRescue@gmail.com to set up a meet and greet with Ruby! 1/31/22 1:08 PM

animal.name: Balto
animal.description:
Some pets are in the Shelter and others in Foster homes. Scroll thru description for preferred contact info!!
Additionally for CATS you may email latkinson@eulesstx.gov and for DOGS, email trinitygapclub@gmail.com

Balto is SUCH the gentleman. He is a very easy going, kind, gorgeous and well behaved 5-6 year old pittie/Black Mouth Cur mix. He has beautiful coloring. He is heart worm positive, but don't let that deter you from this near perfect guy. Trinity GAP will cover the cost of his heart worm treatment so no worries there!!
He was found as a stray in Euless. We noticed how bad his front teeth were and took him to a vet for a dental. The vet said he had spent extended periods of time in a kennel as the teeth were worn from chewing on metal! This poor dog has spent too much time confined in a metal crate. Because of that time, he hates being in a kennel, so much so that he is an escape artist. His foster mom has come home to find him on the couch, tail thumping, and the kennel wide open. He has never chewed on anything while loose and doesn't go the bathroom. After getting out during the night, his foster mom gave up trying to kennel him and installed a dog door so he had access to the backyard. Because of that he would do best in a home with a dog door or access to outside, but that means no pool or anyway he could hurt himself outside.
Balto is a very well behaved guy. This dog just LOVES laying on the couch. He is a total couch potato. He loves cuddling with you on the couch or just being there by himself. He just appreciates his FREEDOM and not being confined in a kennel. He does well with medium or smaller dogs, but might not be the best choice with larger dogs especially dogs he finds a little irritating. He is a very laid back guy so a large dog 'getting in his face' doesn't set well with him. He is learning how to walk on a leash and doing surprisingly well considering he was most likely not taken for a lot of walks in his past. He is not a big chewer of toys and doesn't want anything to do with a ball or playing fetch. He basically likes to. Lay on the couch. He is great with children, very patient and not hyper or excited. He is also great with cats!! Cats love him and he is generally scared of them! HAHAHA!! If you have a dog loving cat, he would do great in your home.
Come meet this gorgeous sweet big boy!
lisacassell@yahoo.com

Kassie was brought into the shelter during the holidays very malnourished, sick and scared. She truly broke our hearts. Through it all, she was an angel. Kassie Is s black mouth cur with a sweet and loving dog personality who will make a great forever friend. She now look great. She is a good eater and has gained weight due to the three meals a day her foster feeds her. She loves being outside, but is crate or room trained to sleep in her bed and is also potty trained. Being only 18 months old, Kassie does still chew on things, but we are working on that and making good progress. She has lots of chew toys and can self entertain. She is such a fun girl. Kassie is also very smart and knows her basic commands: sit, shake, and sit pretty. She greets all with a big smile and is joyful to everyone she meets. Kassie is good with other dogs but she would be a fine solo dog too. She will be spayed February 8 now that she is at a healthy weight, and her heartworm treatment will be done a couple of weeks later. Our vet said since she is young, she has no damage to her heart and will recover quickly from treatment to be a healthy girl who should live a long full life. If you would like to meet Kassie, please email steffeniegaprescue@gmail.com

Shadow is a 9 month old pit bull and black lab mix (we think). He is a really great dog who would be a great addition to any family! He is very calm (most of the time), but likes to play in the mornings. He loves toys with squeakers and tries to destroy them as fast as possible! He is great in the car, good on a leash and super patient with children. He loves to meet other dogs when we are walking, so I assume he will be fine in a home with other animals. He is house trained (with only a few mistakes) and crate trained (even though he doesn't really like it). He knows basic commands like 'come' and 'sit' and seems pretty intelligent to pick up others. He is still a puppy, so there is a little bit of curiosity and sneakiness when it comes to food on a counter or table. He has learned not to grab food or beg since coming to us, but will not pass up an opportunity if presented with unguarded food. He is really the best dog and I know anyone who gets him for his forever home will love him!

animal.description:
Some pets are in the Shelter and others in Foster homes. Scroll thru description for preferred contact info!!
Additionally for CATS you may email latkinson@eulesstx.gov and for DOGS, email trinitygapclub@gmail.com

Are you looking for the perfect senior girl? Look no further than Chloe! Chloe is a 55 lb hound mix. She is the sweetest of sweet and everyone who meets her loves her instantly! She lives with her 2 foster brothers and foster sister and gets along great with everyone. She once met a cat at the pet store and was cautiously curious until the cat hissed at her and then she started barking at the cat from a safe distance. She would probably be fine with an even-tempered cat.

Chloe was surrendered by her owner without reason. Unfortunately, during vetting, we discovered that Chloe is heartworm positive. But don't let that deter you! Chloe is being treated for heartworms and we are committed to making sure that she becomes heartworm free!

At 11, Chloe is well into her senior years, but she doesn't let age define her! She walks very well on a leash. She quite enjoys the pet store, where she would walk up and down the aisles for hours if you let her. She enjoys short strolls through the neighborhood, as well. In the mornings she can often be seen running around the backyard with her 2-year-old foster brother, spreading all the neighborhood gossip through the canine channels. When she isn't gossiping at the fence line, Chloe likes to take lots of naps and play with stuffed toys.

If you think you are a good fit for Chloe and would like more information, contact Jenifer at FabEulessFosterMom@yahoo.com

Some pets are in the Shelter and others in Foster homes. Scroll thru description for preferred contact info!!
Additionally for CATS you may email latkinson@eulesstx.gov and for DOGS, email trinitygapclub@gmail.com

Meet Miss Rosie. 7 year old Rosie was found walking in circles outside a convenience store in Euless. She was starving and almost dead from malnutrition and a severe case of heartworms. Trinity GAP rushed her to our vet and with some good food, vitamins and lots of TLC from her foster. She has now fully recovered and is a healthy girl ready for her forever family. We have no idea what Rosie has suffered but she is a little shy at first but warms up to anyone who will give her a little time and lots of TLC. Rosie is potty trained and does well with other dogs. She is a sweet soul and is patiently waiting for someone to give her the best life ever. Contact Steffenie steffeniegaprescue@gmail.com

animal.name: Leila
animal.description:
Some pets are in the Shelter and others in Foster homes. Scroll thru description for preferred contact info!!
Additionally for CATS you may email latkinson@eulesstx.gov and for DOGS, email trinitygapclub@gmail.com

Meet Leila! She is a Texas Blue Lacy mix, the state dog of Texas. As with most of the breed, she is loving, energetic and plays well dogs of similar energy. Leila weighs around 45 pounds and enjoys playing with toys, but her favorite thing is to run and play by herself or with other dogs. She would make an excellent running companion or agility dog. Leila loves people and attention but has a lot of energy for young children. She will do better with older children and adults. Leila has a unique and beautiful color. Blue Lacys can be blue, brownish red and even brindle. Leila's coat is a beautiful mix of blue and fawn colors. Just gorgeous! The vet said she might have some cattle dog in her, hence the ears. Leila walks on a leash but is so excited to be out and about that she may need a little training not to pull. Leila is a very smart dog and will blossom with a little exercise, time and a loving home. She is potty trained and kennel trained. Leila is heartworm negative, vaccinated and spayed. We would love to get this sweetheart out of boarding and into a home. If you would like to foster or adopt Leila, please contact evegapfoster1@yahoo.com

animal.name: Gigi
animal.description:
Please contact Trinity GAP Club (trinitygapclub@gmail.com) for more information about this pet.Some pets are in the Shelter and others in Foster homes. Scroll thru description for preferred contact info!!
Additionally for CATS you may email latkinson@eulesstx.gov and for DOGS, email trinitygapclub@gmail.com

Hi everyone! My name is Gigi and I am a 60 pound, spayed, and potty trained female American Staffordshire terrier. Even though I am 8 years old, you would never guess it because I have so much energy to share and am a puppy at heart. My favorite pastimes include chewing on bones and treats, rolling around, scampering and sniffing around the yard, basking in the sunshine, and napping alongside and loving on my humans. Even though I've had a hard life, I hold no grudges- I am a people-dog at heart and will make that known quickly. I'm a big baby and will even hug you and enjoy when I'm cradled. I need all the love and attention on me, so I would do best as an only dog in the house. I am a very smart girl! I know my name, when to sit, stay, get down, go outside, among other commands. I am a polite and quiet girl, but am sure to show you how excited I am with zoomies and endless tail wagging. Be ready for all the love, cuddles, nose boops, and kisses from me (and be ready to give them too)! My foster momma says I am the goodest girl ever and a giver of happiness, I have so much love to share with a loving forever home. Give me a chance and I'll be your companion for life!
steffeniegaprescue@gmail.com
1/30/22 8:10 PM

animal.name: Zara
animal.description:
Please contact Michelle (mssquared@hotmail.com) for more information about this pet.Some pets are in the Shelter and others in Foster homes. Scroll thru description for preferred contact info!!
Additionally for CATS you may email latkinson@eulesstx.gov and for DOGS, email trinitygapclub@gmail.com

Zara

Lab- terrier mix

Birthdate 11/12/17

Zara is a very sweet and loving 3-year-old girl. She'll put her head on your chest and give you a hug. She might even sneak in some kisses. She loves to eat and is sure to remind you when it's mealtime. Zara sits politely for a treat - her favorite being a few animal crackers.

She loves to run around the yard and chase tennis balls (she even brings them back)! Zara really enjoys long walks in the park. She's very good on a leash but may get distracted by a squirrel or two.

Zara is not a fan of loud noises or thunderstorms. She'll find a quiet space to hang out until the storm passes by.

Plays well with dogs of the same size in outdoor social settings. Can be a little bossy and bark at those playing around her. Very vocal when she plays, but not necessarily in a mean way. she would do best as the only dog in a home with older or no children.

While not a fan of primping, she'll let you trim her toenails a couple at a time. Zara is low maintenance when it comes to grooming but she does love a good belly rub.

She's a smart girl!! She's both crate trained and house trained. Zara has excelled at her obedience classes since she was a pup. She knows her name and will come when called. Zara can sit, lay down, stay, heel and stand all on command among a few other things. She doesn't jump on people, but you know she's happy to see you by her smile and the boop of her nose!

She's up to date on all her shots and had a clean bill of health at her last check up. Zara is already spayed and microchipped.

This lovable girl will make a great companion!
email evegapfoster1@yahoo.com
